==Demography==
According to the [[2017 Census of Pakistan|2017 census]], the total population of the district stands at 420,624.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://nation.com.pk/national/27-Aug-2017/census-2017-ajk-population-rises-to-over-4m|title=Census 2017: AJK population rises to over 4m|work=The Nation|access-date=2017-09-01|language=en-US}}</ref>

== Education ==

According to the ''Alif Ailaan Pakistan District Education Rankings'' ''2015'', Bhimber ranked 10th out of 145 districts in Pakistan in terms of  education. For facilities and infrastructure, the district is ranked 116 out of 145.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.data.com.pk/edurankings/district.php?distid=19003&proid=19&yearid=3|title=Individual district profile link, 2015|publisher=Alif Ailaan|accessdate=2015-05-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304052014/http://www.data.com.pk/edurankings/district.php?distid=19003&proid=19&yearid=3|archive-date=2016-03-04|url-status=dead}}</ref>

==Climate==

The southern zone Mirpur Division has a similar climate to the neighbouring areas of Punjab, hot summer temperature is often over 45 C from May to September and cold winter, rainfall is concentrated in the monsoon from late June to the end of August.  There is often a prolonged dry period from October to early January followed by Winter rains from mid-January to March.

